DOC request for sentence clarification.
Received and filed:  Original Transcript of  SENTENCING Proceedings commencing AUGUST 28, 2014  (32 pages) and Certification of Filing Transcript.

Defendant Sharod Antoina Doll in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Defendant Sharod Antoina Doll in custody.  Erin M. Karshen and Kevin Shomin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Clerk;ds

Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by counsel and defendant. On motion of the State, Court reads-in three unissued charges for sentencing purposes.  

COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms, he must provide a DNA sample if not previously provided and pay the DNA surcharge and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 2 years with 208 days credit -  consecutive - INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 1 year  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 1 year; pay costs, assessments and surcharges by the end of the sentence or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay any monetary amounts ordered but not paid while in the institution; 3) AODA, programs or treatment; 4) no illegally controlled substances; 5) random screening; 6) seek and maintain employment; 7) no contact with the victim without her consent.

Court finds defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant must comply with the sex offender reporting requirements for 15 years; 
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis and pay the surcharge - if not already done
-  DOC to collect those monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of funds;
- restitution set at -0-.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
Bail argued by counsel.  Court denies motion.

Defendant waives constitutional rights, enters a plea of GUILTY to the amended charge and is examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum  received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the Complaint as a factual basis for judgment.  Court finds defendant guilty as charged in the Amended  Information and enters a judgment of conviction.

Parties advised the Court will listen to statements by counsel, victim, a friend or relative of the defendant and defendant.  Any other statements must be in writing and provided to the Court 72 hours in advance of sentencing.  Because of the possibility of incarceration, the defendant should be prepared to begin serving the sentence at the next date.  Restitution will be addressed at that time.

Court orders the defendant remanded into the custody of the sheriff pending sentencing.
